Install python and pip

Installing virtualenvwrapper for specific projecrt
***pip install virtualenvwrapper-win

Create Envirnment in PC
***mkvirtualenv test
test is envirnment name

Install Django
***pip install django

Create Folder
***mkdir prject
cd projects

Create Project
***django-admin startproject BookTable
	cd/BookTable
	
Run Project
***python manage.py runserver

User Virtual Envirnment
***workon test

StartApp Development
***python manage.py startapp projectname





#####Setup Static Files#####
Create static folder in project
paste all static files-images,js,jquery etc

DO following in settings.py
-STATICFILES_DIRS=[
			os.path.join(BASE_DIR,'projectfolder/static')
			
		]
#to improve process django put all static file in django assets folder	
 STATIC_ROOT=os.path.join(BASE_DIR,'assets')

***In command line do following thing***
***python manage.py collectstatic

***Now edit html page
	At top of file write:
	{% load static %}

***You have to do Following jinja tag everywhere in href to connect all static files
	href="{% static url  %}" 


Do edinding models.py for dynamic binding with database and UI
Create class and data variables


Create Object in  Viws.py of class defined in models.py


##For images 
	at top of page:{% static "images" as baseURL %}
	
	in actual tage:src="{{baseURL}}/{{obj.img}}"

